<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="52" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Material.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="52">-Holotype female: ANGOLA: Moxico and Bihe distr., Upper Luena River (NHMUK).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="52">
-Differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. munda" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" rank="species" species="munda">R. munda</taxonomicName>
in narrower, longer antennae and in shorter metazona of pronotum with a straighter hind margin (for further details see under 
<taxonomicName genus="Acridina" lsidName="Acridina munda" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" rank="species" species="munda">munda</taxonomicName>
). Coloration as in the brachypterous form of 
<taxonomicName genus="Acridina" lsidName="Acridina munda" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" rank="species" species="munda">munda</taxonomicName>
. Micropterous. Table 5 gives morphometric data for 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. angusticornis" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" rank="species" species="angusticornis">R. angusticornis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="52">
-Nothing published on its bionomics, but likely to be similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. munda" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" rank="species" species="munda">R. munda</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
